WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.160
Let's deploy a Streamlit web app together.

00:00:02.160 --> 00:00:06.600
I built the Streamlit web app as a UI to surface my machine learning model, so now let's deploy

00:00:06.600 --> 00:00:10.000
it so our non-technical stakeholders can use this model super easily.

00:00:10.000 --> 00:00:12.320
I like using Connect Cloud because of how simple it is.

00:00:12.320 --> 00:00:15.840
My background is in data science, and I want to make deployment as easy as possible, and

00:00:15.840 --> 00:00:17.799
Connect Cloud is doing exactly that.

00:00:17.799 --> 00:00:21.559
All you have to do is log in using your existing GitHub account, select the repository where

00:00:21.559 --> 00:00:26.000
you built your application, make sure you've uploaded your requirements.txt file in the

00:00:26.000 --> 00:00:29.879
repository so Connect Cloud knows exactly what packages to install when running your app,

00:00:29.879 --> 00:00:30.879
then you click deploy.

00:00:30.879 --> 00:00:34.200
It only takes a few minutes to spin up, and then your application is live and ready for

00:00:34.200 --> 00:00:35.200
use.

00:00:35.200 --> 00:00:38.200
Connect Cloud can also double as your personal portfolio, so make sure you're uploading all

00:00:38.200 --> 00:00:39.200
of your projects here.

00:00:39.200 --> 00:00:42.200
Leave any questions in the comments below, and follow along for more data science content.

00:00:42.200 --> 00:00:42.700
Bye!

